Six-time Grammy-nominated composer Vincent Le Carl Berry II will hold a Cookout Africa songwriting masterclass designed for the music industry of Eastern Africa tomorrow. He will do so at the Intra-African Trade Fair (IATF) 2021. It is a live collaborative songwriting experience meant to engage participants in creative writing, group function, reflection, peer learning, peer interaction and practice. Vincent is inviting upcoming and professional songwriters from Eastern Africa to sign-up for the interactive session between Eastern African based songwriters and himself. Vincent Berry II is celebrated for being the lead writer of ‘Sandcastles’, on Beyonce’s highly acclaimed project 'Lemonade' that provoked an intense worldwide discussion about race, feminism, social media and the music industry. He is honoured to be part of the 59th Grammy Award-winning project.